history.text: Hello
Hello!
Heard of any good movies?
I really like Toy Story, have you seen it?
Oh, yes, I have seen that.  It is good.
my kids really enjoy it, I think its a classic
My son loves it.  Do you know what year it was released?
It was released in 1995. Wow seems so long ago
Tom Hanks is also a fvorite actor of mine. I love him in this movie
Yes, it does.  I did not see it for several years because I did not have a child yet.  Once I saw it with my son, I loved it.
Tom Hanks is great.  I also liked Tim Allen's character.
Yeah, Tim Allen is amazing as well. A lot of good actors in this one
Woody was always my favorite, but i love buzz to
Do you know the Rotten Tomato score for the movie?
9/10 was there average
it scored really well
Oh, it should be 10/10.
I guess a perfect score is too much to ask.
id give it a perfect score if it was me
Wasn't that a Pixar movie or did that name come later?
I believe it was a pixar animation
i think it was the first feature film produced by pixar
Great.  Do you know if it won any awards?
Im not real sure if it won any awards or not. Id have to find out about that one
Gotcha.  I'm sure it probably won something.
id think so as well
I think that would be a good movie to see again over spring break with my son.
Yes we own it on DVD, it is one to watch over and over and never gets old
The kids love seeing the toys come to life
My son used to have this Buzz Lightyear figure that talked.
Yeah we have several of the toys. My mom actually has a woody toy that talks from when it first came out, Its pretty neat
My son had that one, too.  It had a pull string on back.
